objenome.solver.evolve

Class AbstractOrganismOperator

  • java.lang.Object
    • objenome.solver.evolve.AbstractOrganismOperator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GPContainer.GPContainerAware, OrganismOperator
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    OnePointCrossover, PointMutation, Reproduction, SubtreeCrossover, SubtreeMutation

    public abstract class AbstractOrganismOperator
extends java.lang.Object
implements OrganismOperator
    A skeletal implementation of the OrganismOperator interface than fires events at the start (before) and end (after) the operator is performed. Typically, subclasses will override one of the following methods:
    • perform(Organism...): when no custom end event is needed;
    • perform(OperatorEvent.EndOperator, Organism...): when a custom end event is used, this method should be overridden to set the additional information.
    See Also:
    Event, EventManager, Listener

      • perform

        public Organism[] perform(OperatorEvent.EndOperator event,
                          Organism... individuals)
        Performs the operator on the specified individuals. If the operator is not successful, the specified individuals will not be changed and null is returned. The default implementation calls the perform(Organism...) method.

        When overriding this method, the specified EndOperator event can be used to provide more information about the operator. In order to do so, the getEndEvent(Organism...) method must return a custom event instance, enabling this method to set its properties.

        Parameters:
        event - the end event object to be fired after this operator is performed.
        individuals - the individuals undergoing the operator.
        Returns:
        the indivuals produced by this operator.
        See Also:
        getEndEvent(Organism...)

      • perform

        public Organism[] perform(Organism... individuals)
        Performs the operator on the specified individuals. If the operator is not successful, the specified individuals will not be changed and null is returned. The default implementation just returns the same individuals.

      • getEndEvent

        protected OperatorEvent.EndOperator getEndEvent(Organism... parents)
